This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating natural language descriptions for images. It also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) to extract image features, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNN) to generate sentences, which falls under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. 

The addition of memory cells to gate the feeding of image features is a novel approach that involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper involves experiments on datasets, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
